# React Boilerplate
Yet another reactjs boilerplate

## Feature and Library
- reactjs
- babel (es2015, stage-2, react, jsx-transform)
- redux
- redux-saga
- redux-batched-actions
  To prevent react render multiple times on dispatching multiple action
- redux-actions
  To simplify action & reducer creation
- node-sass
- chunk module loading
- appcache
- webworker
- hot reload
- webpack
- webpack chunks
- html-webpack-plugin
  For automaticaly html creation
- offline-plugin
  For automaticaly generate appcache.manifest


## Structure(s)
|--+ components -> Stateless component(s) / dump component(s)
|  |- component1.jsx
|  |- component2.jsx
|  \- component(n).jsx
|
|--+ containers -> Component that have access to redux actions
|  |--+ app
|  |  |- index.jsx
|  |  |- reducer.js
|  |  |- actions.js
|  |  |- constants.js
|  |  +- sagas.js
|  |
|  \--+ sidebar
|     |- index.jsx
|     |--+ reducers
|     |  |- reducer1.js
|     |  |- reducer2.js
|     |  \- reducer(n).js
|     |- actions.js
|     |- constants.js
|     \--+ sagas
|        |- sagas1.js
|        |- sagas(n).js
|
|--+ reducers -> Combined reducers
|  \- index.js
|
|--+ sagas -> Combined sagas
|  \- index.js
|
|--+ store -> Redux store related file(s)
|  \- index.js
|
|- index.js -> Webpack entry point
\- webpack.config.js

## Rules
- Every javascript file that contain jsx must be named .jsx
- Using jscs node-style
- Using editorconfig
